                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At the 257th meeting of the Austrian Deputies on September 7, Zarubin took the
                    same line as at previous meetings and “after a mutual exchange of
                    recriminations” the British Deputy proposed, and the United States and French
                    Deputies accepted, a proposal to suspend the meetings until mid-December.
                    Zarubin agreed to consult his Government and inform the Secretariat whether this
                    procedure could be adopted. (Telegram 1454, <gloss target="#t_Delau1"
                        >Delau</gloss> 487, September 7, from London, 663.001/9–750)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
